<br>
AOW Rule:<br>
<br>
The AOW may be attempted upon your turn at the Statue, at no other time unless given permission by the guild currently up for it will the AOW be engaged by a guild trying to enter the rotation. <br>
<br>
Planes, Fear, Sky, Hate:<br>
<br>
Any guild caught &quot;cleaning up&quot; on nights when a guild has already been there on respawns (IE guild goes in early clears fear, and another guild comes in and cleans up on respawn pushing the respawn time back for the next guild) will be assessed a 30 day penalty on the calender, during which said reserves will be removed and redone.<br>
<br>
Going into a plane on a day that another guild has it reserved without their permission will be assessed the same 30 day penalty.<br>
<br>
TOV and multiple mob rots:<br>
<br>
When a guild gets onto a rotation, it is not acceptable for another guild to go in after they are done and clean up what is left. any guild caught doing so will be assessed the penalty of losing their current rot turn and next rot turn on said rotation if they are not on said rotation a suitable punishment will be worked out on a case by case basis.<br>
<br>
Entering the Glyphed/Exiled/Cursed rotation.<br>
<br>
A force of 40 members must be in the zone before the first taskmaster is killed for the rotation guild to back off and allow you an attempt. Any killing to stall will not be tolerated. Gaining access to the rotation is only done by killing both the Glyphed and Exiled on one Turn, you cannot do a Exiled after someone else has done the Glyphed and his PH has respawned. If you fail to the Gylphed or Exiled or are unable to spawn them they will pass to the guild that is up for the kill on rotation.<br>
<br>
Cursed rules:<br>
<br>
Upon entering the Glyphed/Exiled rotation a guild may make 2 attempts at killing cursed on their day of the cycle. These attempts must be done first thing upon the mobs being known up and if unsuccessful should let the guild currently up for cleanup or an RTA admin know.  These attempts can only be done on your turn at the Glyphed/Exiled spawn, not at any other time unless ffa is called on the mobs. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Have a Nice Day - Management</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=theadmin@therathetravelagency>TheAdmin</A> at: 1/30/03 8:47:44 pm<br></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#00FFFF>- </font><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency>The Rathe Travel Agency Board</a><font color=#00FFFF> - </font><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11>Guild Representatives Forum</a> <font color=#00FFFF> - </font><a href="http://www.jakefitch.com/rta/Calendar.asp">The Rathe Calendar</a><font color=#00FFFF> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.107<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.<br>Accelerated By <a href="http://www.wbs.com/ezboard.html">JXEL</a></center></body></html>  

